167-163 West 94th Street, north side, east of Amsterdam Avenue.
About 1911.

714859f-a.text:
171 to 165 W. 94th Street, north side, east of Amsterdam Avenue, snowing at the left center, a building that is being converted into a Buddhist Temple by the New York Buddhist Church and which will be conducted by Hozen Seki of No. 121 W. 79th Street.
This individual and his wife have been conducting similar services at their home for the last year and state that this new place of worship will be the first of its kind in the eastern part of this country.
For a fuller descriptive account see the New York Times of
June 3, 1958.
View No. 2 is the same from another angle.
May 9, 1938
Views 1 and 2
George D. Chinn
